Definition.WordDefinition:
Swedish \Swed"ish\, a. [Cf. G. schwedisch, Sw. svensk.] Of or pertaining to Sweden or its inhabitants. [1913 Webster]
{Swedish turnip}. (Bot.) See under {Turnip}. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Swedish \Swed"ish\, n. The language of Swedes. [1913 Webster]

Swedish adj : of or relating to or characteristic of Sweden or its people or culture or language; "the Swedish King"; "Swedish punch"; "Swedish umlauts" n : a Scandinavian language that is the official language of Sweden and one of two official languages of Finland
